And at the same time. this
guy named Sean Trende.

747
00:31:10.168 --> 00:31:12.804
who's a lawyer. writes
a two or three-part series

748
00:31:12.871 --> 00:31:14.005
for RealClearPolitics.

749
00:31:14.138 --> 00:31:15.974
- I heard Barack Obama
make the comment.

750
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:18.843
"You guys have to
appeal to non-white voters

751
00:31:18.977 --> 00:31:20.812
or you'll never win
another election."

752
00:31:20.879 --> 00:31:22.080
I just thought that's not right.

753
00:31:22.180 --> 00:31:24.048
So I wrote this
column about. actually.

754
00:31:24.182 --> 00:31:28.386
if the GOP could figure out a
way to appeal to white voters

755
00:31:28.519 --> 00:31:30.088
and increase their
vote share there.

756
00:31:30.188 --> 00:31:33.524
they could more
than offset their losses

757
00:31:33.658 --> 00:31:34.826
among non-white voters.

758
00:31:34.893 --> 00:31:37.495
And so that's the idea
of the missing whites.

759
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:39.197
- And so Trende's thing
was quite interesting to me.

760
00:31:39.330 --> 00:31:41.532
about the whole white
working class element of it.

761
00:31:41.666 --> 00:31:43.902
and how. really. both
parties had abandoned it.

762
00:31:44.035 --> 00:31:45.270
It was pretty obvious to me.

763
00:31:45.370 --> 00:31:47.038
It kind of reinforced
what I felt.

764
00:31:47.105 --> 00:31:49.007
- There were a lot of
white voters out there

765
00:31:49.073 --> 00:31:50.508
that were gettable for the GOP.

766
00:31:50.575 --> 00:31:51.609
that. for whatever reason.

767
00:31:51.709 --> 00:31:54.212
the Republicans weren't
pulling them to the polls.

768
00:31:54.345 --> 00:31:56.180
- [Interviewer] So you
come out with this strategy.

769
00:31:56.247 --> 00:31:58.449
how do people
respond to it publicly?

770
00:31:58.549 --> 00:31:59.751
- Oh. they hated it.

771
00:31:59.884 --> 00:32:02.053
- I had a dinner with Jeff
Sessions and Stephen Miller.

772
00:32:02.186 --> 00:32:04.188
Senator Sessions.
let's say this.

773
00:32:04.255 --> 00:32:06.724
had a few bourbon
and branches. okay?

774
00:32:06.858 --> 00:32:07.859
A lot.

775
00:32:07.926 --> 00:32:09.294
And we go through those policies

776
00:32:09.394 --> 00:32:14.232
that we believe
strongly is what's needed

777
00:32:14.299 --> 00:32:16.200
to drive the Republican
Party to actually start

778
00:32:16.267 --> 00:32:17.869
to get a electoral majority.

779
00:32:17.936 --> 00:32:21.306
- And they went over some
election analysis by John Trende.

780
00:32:21.406 --> 00:32:23.574
and they interpreted
this analysis to mean

781
00:32:23.708 --> 00:32:28.279
that they could launch
a popular movement.

782
00:32:28.413 --> 00:32:30.114
- [Interviewer] How
did the three of you.

783
00:32:30.248 --> 00:32:34.052
what's your game plan to push
back on immigration reform?

784
00:32:34.118 --> 00:32:35.320
- We have to stop it now.

785
00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:36.955
We know something's
gonna come up that year.

786
00:32:37.088 --> 00:32:41.926
- If this were to pass.
wages would go down.

787
00:32:41.993 --> 00:32:43.661
unemployment would go up.

788
00:32:43.761 --> 00:32:45.930
- We knew we had to stop it.
We had to stop it legislatively.

789
00:32:45.997 --> 00:32:47.098
and we thought we could stop it.

790
00:32:47.165 --> 00:32:48.299
- [Interviewer]

791
00:32:48.433 --> 00:32:50.835
- Well. first off. there
were articles every day.

792
00:32:50.935 --> 00:32:53.304
There was everybody
on radio shows and TV.

793
00:32:53.438 --> 00:32:54.639
We really pushed the thing out.

794
00:32:54.772 --> 00:32:56.975
- We should be taking
immigrants who are better than us.

795
00:32:57.108 --> 00:32:58.176
not worse than us.

796
00:32:58.276 --> 00:33:00.011
But instead of
skimming the cream.

797
00:33:00.111 --> 00:33:03.114
we are scraping the
bottom of the barrel.

798
00:33:03.247 --> 00:33:05.416
taking care of other
countries' internal problems.

799
00:33:05.483 --> 00:33:08.686
Taking their terrorists. their
losers. their poor people.

800
00:33:08.786 --> 00:33:13.424
- I had a phone interview
with Steve Bannon in 2014.

801
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:16.661
I was walking around
Barnes & Noble in Lynchburg.

802
00:33:16.794 --> 00:33:20.031
and he was just firing
off questions. like he does.

803
00:33:20.131 --> 00:33:23.468
And he said. "What's your
perspective on education?"

804
00:33:23.601 --> 00:33:25.370
And I would just
deliver. you know.

805
00:33:25.470 --> 00:33:27.338
the true believer
conservative lines.

806
00:33:27.472 --> 00:33:31.275
And then he said. "What do
you think about immigration?"

807
00:33:31.342 --> 00:33:33.644
All I said was. "It
affects everything."

808
00:33:35.313 --> 00:33:37.815
He was so excited and
enthused by that answer.

809
00:33:37.949 --> 00:33:39.517
he yelled. "Yes!"

810
00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:40.885
And I heard him
through the phone.

811
00:33:40.985 --> 00:33:42.286
I actually pulled
it away a little bit.

812
00:33:42.353 --> 00:33:45.056
Like. okay. he's really
excited about that.

813
00:33:45.156 --> 00:33:46.991
And I was hired like that.

814
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:48.359
- We kind of put
a network together

815
00:33:48.493 --> 00:33:51.362
of people that just continued

816
00:33:51.496 --> 00:33:53.564
to put out more and
more information.

817
00:33:53.664 --> 00:33:56.200
Look. our whole thing is
if you put out information

818
00:33:56.334 --> 00:33:59.037
and you have force
multipliers to just drive it.

819
00:33:59.170 --> 00:34:00.571
people will start to
absorb it themselves.

820
00:34:00.671 --> 00:34:03.341
- It's the servant class
that is coming in who-

821
00:34:03.474 --> 00:34:06.144
- But we're losing workers.
- taxpayers need to support.

822
00:34:06.210 --> 00:34:07.845
- For everyone
who's a valedictorian.

823
00:34:07.979 --> 00:34:09.213
there's another 100 out there

824
00:34:09.347 --> 00:34:11.649
that they weigh 130 pounds.

825
00:34:11.716 --> 00:34:13.418
and they've got calves
the sides of cantaloupes

826
00:34:13.518 --> 00:34:15.820
because they're hauling
75 pounds of marijuana

827
00:34:15.887 --> 00:34:17.021
across the desert.

828
00:34:17.088 --> 00:34:18.156
- I mean. it's the.
what do they say?

829
00:34:18.222 --> 00:34:20.158
You know. the Russian
active measures.

830
00:34:20.224 --> 00:34:23.194
It's. you know. lying
through a fire hose.

831
00:34:23.327 --> 00:34:25.496
I mean. you're just
overwhelmed by the lies.

832
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:27.698
- A lot of the people coming
into the country are working

833
00:34:27.832 --> 00:34:29.167
for drug cartels.

834
00:34:29.233 --> 00:34:31.936
A lot of the people have
wreaked havoc upon communities.

835
00:34:32.036 --> 00:34:35.273
- The strategy was
to take reactionary.

836
00:34:35.373 --> 00:34:38.076
racist feelings
against immigrants.

837
00:34:40.011 --> 00:34:41.245
you know. non-white immigrants.

838
00:34:41.379 --> 00:34:43.548
and to present it to the base

839
00:34:43.681 --> 00:34:49.120
as a political choice made
by elites who betrayed you.

840
00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:50.788
the working white man.

841
00:34:50.888 --> 00:34:53.458
- [Critic] Do you realize. we're
the second-class citizens?

842
00:34:53.558 --> 00:34:56.394
You secure that
border to protect us.

843
00:34:56.527 --> 00:34:58.229
- As if we were being deluged

844
00:34:58.362 --> 00:35:01.699
by a wave of
non-white immigrants.

845
00:35:01.766 --> 00:35:03.634
- You're gonna have a
flood of new immigrants

846
00:35:03.734 --> 00:35:04.936
into the United States.

847
00:35:05.069 --> 00:35:07.305
- They're invading. they're
murdering. they're raping.

848
00:35:07.405 --> 00:35:08.739
- As one officer said.

849
00:35:08.873 --> 00:35:11.576
a tidal wave of new
illegality in the future.

850
00:35:11.642 --> 00:35:14.645
- And that successfully
turned public opinion

851
00:35:14.745 --> 00:35:16.414
against immigration.

852
00:35:16.547 --> 00:35:19.150
- This country is being
invaded by foreigners

853
00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:21.385
with diseases and crime.

854
00:35:21.452 --> 00:35:23.554
- These are gonna be
more jobs taken away.

855
00:35:23.621 --> 00:35:25.490
- Letting Muslims
come across the border.

856
00:35:25.590 --> 00:35:27.391
They are finding
Qurans on the ground.

857
00:35:27.458 --> 00:35:30.061
- When I hear. "Let's go
after the missing white voter."

858
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:31.395
I start to think. "Oh Lord."

859
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:32.830
- There's an
article in the nation

860
00:35:32.930 --> 00:35:36.234
where one of their editors
called me a white supremacist.

861
00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:38.102
A lot of people
took the suggestion

862
00:35:38.236 --> 00:35:41.472
that this is a path that
the GOP could take.

863
00:35:42.607 --> 00:35:44.308
as me basically
calling for the GOP

864
00:35:44.442 --> 00:35:47.678
to be the party of white people.

865
00:35:47.778 --> 00:35:50.648
and that's absolutely
not what I wanted.

866
00:35:50.781 --> 00:35:52.817
It was kind of an
academic exercise.

867
00:35:52.950 --> 00:35:55.253
I'm just saying. if you wanna
look at the cold calculus

868
00:35:55.319 --> 00:35:57.321
of electoral politics. it
works out a little different

869
00:35:57.455 --> 00:35:59.190
than I think a lot
of people expect.

870
00:35:59.290 --> 00:36:00.691
So it was. like. in 2013

871
00:36:00.791 --> 00:36:02.827
when I was getting all
these attacks. I thought.

872
00:36:02.960 --> 00:36:05.363
"Wouldn't it be great in 2016
if a candidate came along

873
00:36:05.463 --> 00:36:08.599
and did this and
proved me right?"

874
00:36:08.666 --> 00:36:12.937
And then the monkey's
paw finger curled.

875
00:36:13.004 --> 00:36:14.872
because I did not
have Donald Trump

876
00:36:14.972 --> 00:36:16.440
or anyone like him in mind.

877
00:36:16.507 --> 00:36:18.709
And he came and
kind of took the strategy

878
00:36:18.809 --> 00:36:20.778
and put it on steroids.

879
00:36:20.845 --> 00:36:21.646
- [Donald] I'm Donald Trump.

880
00:36:21.712 --> 00:36:23.181
and you're watching
"Fox & Friends."

881
00:36:23.314 --> 00:36:26.284
And if you turn the
channel. you're fired.

882
00:36:26.350 --> 00:36:28.019
- Everyone knows
Trump built an image

883
00:36:28.152 --> 00:36:29.687
of himself via "The Apprentice."

884
00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:31.989
But I believe it was Fox
that was more important

885
00:36:32.123 --> 00:36:33.357
to his political rise.

886
00:36:33.491 --> 00:36:35.059
- Does he have
the power to fire me

887
00:36:35.159 --> 00:36:36.460
in this company?
- Brian. you're fired.

888
00:36:36.527 --> 00:36:37.562
- I guess he doesn't.
- Any further questions?

889
00:36:37.662 --> 00:36:39.197
- Yeah. I guess not.
- Get out.

890
00:36:39.330 --> 00:36:41.332
- Because he was given
by Roger Ailes a weekly slot

891
00:36:41.465 --> 00:36:42.500
on "Fox & Friends."

892
00:36:42.567 --> 00:36:43.834
- You could say that Trump

893
00:36:43.901 --> 00:36:45.970
is the candidate "Fox
& Friends" invented.

894
00:36:46.037 --> 00:36:47.038
(bell ringing)

895
00:36:47.171 --> 00:36:48.005
- I do now.
- Worked out well.

896
00:36:48.139 --> 00:36:49.373
Who's at the door?

897
00:36:49.507 --> 00:36:51.042
Oh look. it's Donald Trump.
Come on in. Mr. Trump.

898
00:36:51.175 --> 00:36:52.543
- [Host] Donald Trump in person.

899
00:36:52.677 --> 00:36:54.545
Every Monday is a
Donald Trump Monday.

900
00:36:54.679 --> 00:36:56.747
but now in person
for one reason:

901
00:36:56.847 --> 00:36:58.149
He hasn't seen Steve
and I in a long time.

902
00:36:58.216 --> 00:36:59.383
- Yeah.
- A long time.

903
00:36:59.517 --> 00:37:00.251
A long time.
- Nice to see you.

904
00:37:00.351 --> 00:37:01.586
Donald Trump.

905
00:37:01.686 --> 00:37:04.388
- He became the GOP
nominee in waiting

906
00:37:04.522 --> 00:37:07.024
because of those weekly
appearances on Fox.

907
00:37:07.091 --> 00:37:12.330
and portrayed himself as
the savior. as the protector.

908
00:37:13.531 --> 00:37:16.500
as the one billionaire
who would save them.

909
00:37:16.567 --> 00:37:17.702
- That's 'cause of you guys.

910
00:37:17.768 --> 00:37:19.070
Donald Trump gets
up in the morning.

911
00:37:19.203 --> 00:37:21.172
tweets to the entire
planet at no cost.

912
00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:22.707
picks up the phone. calls you.

913
00:37:22.773 --> 00:37:25.376
has a great conversation
for about eight minutes.

914
00:37:25.443 --> 00:37:27.445
which would've cost him a
ton in commercial money.

915
00:37:27.545 --> 00:37:29.947
- When Mexico sends its people.

916
00:37:30.047 --> 00:37:31.882
they're not sending their best.

917
00:37:32.016 --> 00:37:35.620
They're not sending you.
They're not sending you.

918
00:37:35.720 --> 00:37:38.723
They're sending people
that have lots of problems.

919
00:37:38.856 --> 00:37:41.192
- Trump was leaning
into the culture war.

920
00:37:41.259 --> 00:37:45.196
He understood how
the people were reacting.

921
00:37:45.263 --> 00:37:46.530
what they were resonating to.

922
00:37:46.597 --> 00:37:47.932
The immigration
was the first one.

923
00:37:48.065 --> 00:37:51.202
- They're bringing drugs.
they're bringing crime.

924
00:37:51.269 --> 00:37:52.570
They're rapists.

925
00:37:52.637 --> 00:37:54.939
And some. I assume.
are good people.

926
00:37:55.072 --> 00:37:56.240
- Political people said.

927
00:37:56.374 --> 00:37:57.642
"Oh. those are very
bad things to say.

928
00:37:57.742 --> 00:37:59.210
That doesn't resonate
with the people."

929
00:37:59.277 --> 00:38:00.645
They missed the boat on that.

930
00:38:00.745 --> 00:38:02.413
That absolutely
resonated with people.

931
00:38:02.546 --> 00:38:06.050
People said. "This guy's
got it. He's absolutely right."

932
00:38:06.117 --> 00:38:07.418
So they wanted to hear more.

933
00:38:07.551 --> 00:38:09.320
- He says what I'm thinking.

934
00:38:09.420 --> 00:38:10.488
- [Participant] Exactly.

935
00:38:10.588 --> 00:38:11.756
- Never been
involved in politics.

936
00:38:11.889 --> 00:38:13.958
Never had an
interest in any of it.

937
00:38:14.091 --> 00:38:16.494
Now. suddenly. he is resonating.

938
00:38:16.594 --> 00:38:18.095
He is resonating
with the people.

939
00:38:18.229 --> 00:38:20.331
and he's speaking our minds.

940
00:38:20.431 --> 00:38:21.565
- He's resonating
with the people.

941
00:38:21.632 --> 00:38:23.601
I've been following
his campaign.

942
00:38:23.734 --> 00:38:25.069
and he's resonating
with the people.

943
00:38:25.136 --> 00:38:26.337
Look at the people.

944
00:38:26.437 --> 00:38:27.738
- [Rick] You would go. and
the people were cheering

945
00:38:27.805 --> 00:38:30.341
like it was some famous
musician coming on stage.

946
00:38:30.441 --> 00:38:33.611
And instead. Trump came
up and he attacked people.

947
00:38:33.744 --> 00:38:40.151
- ISIS is honoring
President Obama.

948
00:38:40.284 --> 00:38:43.821
He is the founder of ISIS.
He's the founder of ISIS. okay?

949
00:38:43.954 --> 00:38:44.955
He's the founder.

950
00:38:46.957 --> 00:38:49.126
He founded ISIS.

951
00:38:49.260 --> 00:38:52.630
- [Rick] And it was almost
like this underlying sentiment

952
00:38:52.697 --> 00:38:53.831
among the American people.

953
00:38:53.964 --> 00:38:57.201
- I want surveillance of
certain mosques. okay?

954
00:38:57.301 --> 00:38:58.636
If that's okay.

955
00:38:58.769 --> 00:39:00.871
- And here's a guy that's
just telling into it plain.

956
00:39:00.971 --> 00:39:02.540
He's not sugarcoating it.

957
00:39:02.640 --> 00:39:04.375
He's using. you
know. abusive words.

958
00:39:04.475 --> 00:39:05.710
whatever you wanna call it.

959
00:39:05.810 --> 00:39:08.279
- Like to punch him
in the face. I'll tell you.

960
00:39:08.346 --> 00:39:09.680
- I met Trump at WrestleMania V.

961
00:39:09.814 --> 00:39:11.115
I'd always been at WrestleMania.

962
00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:13.651
I'd always been a
wrestling WWE fan.

963
00:39:13.784 --> 00:39:15.019
and then through Roger Stone.

964
00:39:15.152 --> 00:39:18.389
was reporting directly to
him. working under Roger.

965
00:39:18.489 --> 00:39:21.492
- Any guy that can do a
body slam. he's my guy.

966
00:39:21.625 --> 00:39:25.396
(audience cheering)

967
00:39:25.496 --> 00:39:27.965
- [Audience] USA. USA!

968
00:39:28.032 --> 00:39:30.568
- We have a movement going.
We have something very special.

969
00:39:30.668 --> 00:39:32.336
- He'd call me. and he's like.
"There's a movement. Sam.

970
00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:34.372
I feel it. It's electrifying.

971
00:39:34.505 --> 00:39:35.906
They love it.
Everyone loves it."

972
00:39:36.006 --> 00:39:38.676
- It was electric to be a
part of one of his rallies.

973
00:39:38.809 --> 00:39:40.845
It really was. It was amazing.

974
00:39:42.680 --> 00:39:45.416
You feel a certain
fellowship and camaraderie

975
00:39:45.516 --> 00:39:49.186
with people who have
like-minded thoughts.

976
00:39:49.253 --> 00:39:50.388
you know. and desires.

977
00:39:50.521 --> 00:39:54.024
And yeah. it was
wonderful. It was amazing.

978
00:39:54.158 --> 00:39:56.360
- It's called "The Snake."

979
00:39:56.494 --> 00:39:58.429
I thought of it having
to do with our borders

980
00:39:58.529 --> 00:39:59.730
and people coming in.

981
00:39:59.864 --> 00:40:01.699
- It was patriotic.
That's all I can say.

982
00:40:01.832 --> 00:40:04.568
He told "The Snake"
poem. and it was wonderful.

983
00:40:04.702 --> 00:40:08.572
- "Oh. shut up. silly woman."

984
00:40:08.706 --> 00:40:11.542
said the reptile with a grin.

985
00:40:11.609 --> 00:40:14.578
"You knew damn
well I was a snake

986
00:40:14.712 --> 00:40:17.882
before you took me in."

987
00:40:17.948 --> 00:40:20.084
- We did some polling
on immigration early on.

988
00:40:20.217 --> 00:40:22.787
and the numbers actually
weren't as supportive

989
00:40:22.887 --> 00:40:24.755
in favor of Trump
as you might think.

990
00:40:24.889 --> 00:40:27.458
It was. do you support
blocking immigration?

991
00:40:27.558 --> 00:40:28.726
